==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Extensometer
<hw>Ex`ten*som"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Extens</ets>ion + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <def>An
instrument for measuring the extension of a body, especially for
measuring the elongation of bars of iron, steel, or other material, when
subjected to a tensile force.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extensor</ent>⟦br⟧
